        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33396",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This may be database specific. As long as the individual select objects for each adapter can either (a) emulate it or (b) discard the state when creating the SQL, it should be okay.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-12T05:52:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-12T05:52:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33397",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'd actually recommend this being a \"forceIndex()\" method, and not a parameter on the from() clause.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-12T05:52:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-12T05:52:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33400",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tunder",
                        "name": "tunder",
                        "displayName": "Ionut Dinu",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "it is indeed a mysql specific statement.\nour DBA told me that there is too an USE INDEX and IGNORE INDEX statement related to this. \nI guess will not be too difficult to implenet an useIndex() and an ignoreIndex() method too.\nthank you and best regards.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tunder",
                        "name": "tunder",
                        "displayName": "Ionut Dinu",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-12T06:54:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-12T06:54:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39658",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yolau",
                        "name": "yolau",
                        "displayName": "Bogdan Martinescu",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I am curious to know the progress on this...\r\nFrom experience I can tell you that having forceindex and useindex as methods is a must have feature for Zend_Db_Select.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yolau",
                        "name": "yolau",
                        "displayName": "Bogdan Martinescu",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-30T10:08:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-30T10:08:54.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40518",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jshpro2",
                        "name": "jshpro2",
                        "displayName": "Josh Ribakoff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Same. What good is a framework if I'd have to replace it when the app becomes popular?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jshpro2",
                        "name": "jshpro2",
                        "displayName": "Josh Ribakoff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-17T21:43:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-17T21:43:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43504",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=richardjohn",
                        "name": "richardjohn",
                        "displayName": "Richard John",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've added support for useIndex and forceIndex for my own purposes, someone else may find this useful.\r\n\r\nAs mentioned above, this is database specific, but my implementation is ignorant to this, and just generates the MySQL syntax.\r\n\r\n\r\nReplacement Zend\/Db\/Select.php:\r\nhttp:\/\/pastie.org\/1354770\r\n\r\nUsage:\r\n\r\n$select->useIndex('index');\r\n\/\/ Or\r\n$select->useIndex(array('index1', 'index2'));\r\n\r\n$select->forceIndex('index');\r\n\/\/ Or\r\n$select->forceIndex(array('index1', 'index2'));\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=richardjohn",
                        "name": "richardjohn",
                        "displayName": "Richard John",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-07T00:07:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-07T00:07:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43506",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bittarman",
                        "name": "bittarman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Mauger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Richard,\r\n\r\nYou will need to sign the CLA before your code submission can be included (and this will also give you the needed permissions to attach patches in the issue tracker).\r\n\r\nOnce you have signed the CLA, could you supply your patch as a svn diff, and also provide unit tests?\r\n\r\nYou will find the needed information about signing the CLA here: http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFPROP\/Contributor+License+Agreement\r\nAnd more information that you may find useful here: http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFDEV\/Contributing+to+Zend+Framework\r\n\r\nSorry I missed you on IRC earlier, I would have given you this info then.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bittarman",
                        "name": "bittarman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Mauger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-07T01:44:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-07T01:44:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43513",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=richardjohn",
                        "name": "richardjohn",
                        "displayName": "Richard John",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Ryan,\r\n\r\nThanks a lot for the info. I'll complete this as soon as I get access to a printer\/scanner.\r\n\r\nI've now reimplemented the functionality to be adapter specific, with hinting for MySQL, SQL Server and Oracle, and written unit tests for it. Hopefully you should get a patch from me in the next few days.\r\n\r\nBest wishes,\r\nRichard",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=richardjohn",
                        "name": "richardjohn",
                        "displayName": "Richard John",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-07T16:11:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-07T16:11:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47542",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bliznaka",
                        "name": "bliznaka",
                        "displayName": "Danail Nedyalkov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Richard,\r\nany progress with the patch?\r\n\r\nDanail Nedyalkov",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bliznaka",
                        "name": "bliznaka",
                        "displayName": "Danail Nedyalkov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-18T18:40:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-18T18:40:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47545",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=richardjohn",
                        "name": "richardjohn",
                        "displayName": "Richard John",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Danail,\r\n\r\nAt the time I emailed my CLA and didn't hear anything back. If there's still interest I can chase it up (could somebody advise who I should email?) and update the patch.\r\n\r\nBest wishes,\r\nRichard",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=richardjohn",
                        "name": "richardjohn",
                        "displayName": "Richard John",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-18T19:26:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-18T19:26:32.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47547",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bliznaka",
                        "name": "bliznaka",
                        "displayName": "Danail Nedyalkov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Richard,\r\nI've got no clue about the email address.  :-(\r\nI use often MySql and really need this patch in official release. I hope that someone will add your patch in next release, until this I will use my own paginator in which I modify the db query. Thanks for the quick response.\r\n\r\nBest wishes,\r\nDanail",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bliznaka",
                        "name": "bliznaka",
                        "displayName": "Danail Nedyalkov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-18T19:42:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-18T19:42:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47548",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=richardjohn",
                        "name": "richardjohn",
                        "displayName": "Richard John",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Daniel,\r\n\r\nIf you require this functionality, a better solution might be to extend Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Mysql, add the method from the patch and use that instead.\r\n\r\nThis is a better place to do it than a paginator, and would mean it wouldn't require any changes (other than optionally switching back to the stock adapter) if this patch finds its way into a release.\r\n\r\nBest wishes,\r\nRichard",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=richardjohn",
                        "name": "richardjohn",
                        "displayName": "Richard John",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-18T20:00:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-18T20:00:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47549",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bliznaka",
                        "name": "bliznaka",
                        "displayName": "Danail Nedyalkov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Richard,\r\nI guess you are right and I'll give it a try, thanks!\r\n\r\nBest wishes,\r\nDanail",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bliznaka",
                        "name": "bliznaka",
                        "displayName": "Danail Nedyalkov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-18T20:08:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-18T20:08:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
